Hello, I'm encountering an issue using the HUBL language to write conditional logic to display if a certain property from a custom object is null OR is equal to a specified value. We've tested various versions of the language including IF and UNLESS statements and still no luck. We want to be able to collapse a table if a condition is met to build a dynamic email template. See language examples below--is this the right way to write conditional logic off a custom object within an email template?

{%
	set Primary = "personalization_token('p7099483_amplero_customer.heroctaurl')"
	%}

{% if Primary =="" %}
{% else %}
{% endif %}

{% unless Primary =="" %}
{% else %}
{% endunless %}
